            <title>[CASSANDRA-19972] Nodetool cms reconfigure reports success when the operation fails due to streaming issues</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-19972</link>
                <project id="12310865" key="CASSANDRA">Apache Cassandra</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;If streaming fails during CMS reconfiguration, the operation enters a &lt;tt&gt;blocked&lt;/tt&gt; state. The operation will still be pending and resumable by an operator &amp;amp; the KPI that indicates the CMS is pending/due reconfiguration will correctly indicate the state. However, the nodetool command itself exits with a success status which is especially problematic in tests.&#160;&lt;br/&gt;
This is easy to repro in an in-jvm dtest by attempting to a CMS reconfiguration without enabling the &lt;tt&gt;NETWORK&lt;/tt&gt; feature on the cluster.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
